news.title: Special court extends builder Sanjay Chhabriaa's CBI remand till Friday
news.para: He was arrested on April 28 in a fraud case related with DHFL promoters — Kapil Wadhawan and Dheeraj Wadhawan — and former promoter of Yes Bank, Rana Kapoor.

news.title: Tata Group chairman buys duplex on Pedder Road for Rs 98 crore
news.para: 33 South, a 28-storey skyscraper, is a high-end condominium near Jaslok Hospital, where the Chandras have been staying on lease for the past five years.

news.title: CBRI team inspects Supertech twin towers
news.para: CBRI, whose help the Supreme Court had asked Noida Authority to take for the demolition process, will prepare a report on their findings and submit it in court.

news.title: In talk with bank to settle dispute over dues: ex-management of Supertech to SC
news.para: "The Interim Resolution Professional (IRP) has stated in the report that there are no sufficient funds in the accounts of the company to be paid to the home buyers of the Twin Towers", he said.

news.title: Bajaj Electricals family buys two apartments on South Mumbai's Carmichael Road
news.para: The deals for both the apartments in Carmichael Residences, with a total 6,344 sq ft of area, is valued at nearly Rs 1.48 lakh per sq ft, a record price being paid for a house anywhere in the country this year.

news.title: Kanpur civic body to take stern action against illegal construction raised by shopowners
news.para: Mayor Pramila Pandey said that municipal commissioner Shiv Sharanappa GN would convene a meeting with deputy chairman Kailash Pandey and would decide whether illegal structure should be demolished or tax be collected along with fine from shopkeepers.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body to send notices to clinics in residential areas for property tax
news.para: The officials claimed they have also started conducting field inspection of hospitals where they are suspecting wrong assessment of tax. By saturday entire process will be complete. As many as 160 hospitals, nursing homes and clinics are served the notices.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes 3,000 shanties along Golf Course Road
news.para: Local goons and land sharks have been charging ocupants— mostly daily wagers, small shopkeepers and domestic staff— a monthly rent of Rs 2,000-Rs 2,500 from the occupants, officials said.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT violated rules by issuing part OC to mall before MPCB nod
news.para: On Tuesday and Wednesday, TOI had reported NIT demolished 35 shops without providing tenants copy of part OC, and violated its own norms in building permit.

news.title: Panel questions Bengaluru development body over poor infra at Kempegowda Layout
news.para: This was the first LPC meeting on the layout following complaints from allottees over the long delay in taking up basic infrastructure work such as underground drainage, water supply and electrification.

news.title: Kochi: Retired high court judge to probe Maradu violations
news.para: The top court directed the state government to provide the necessary facilities and extend all cooperation to Justice Radhakrishnan for completing the inquiry "expeditiously".

news.title: Fire department in Ludhiana issues NOC without proper inspection: Activist
news.para: The NBC of India has classified the buildings based on occupancy like residential, educational, institutional, assembly, business, mercantile, industrial, storage and hazardous categories.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance reports profit of Rs 370 crore in FY22
news.para: Disbursements during the year ending March 31, 2022 grew to Rs 1,641 crore from Rs 1,298 crore registered in the same period last fiscal.

news.title: HC directs Maharashtra govt to refund Rs 23 lakh towards 2% stamp duty to builder
news.para: The ruling will have a big impact on the realty sector all over the state, as registrars had denied concession offered by the state revenue and forest department to many builders for agreements registered between September 1, 2020, and March 3, 2021, said petitioner’s lawyer Kartik Shukul.

news.title: SC asks statutory bodies to hold meeting with Unitech board on approvals & dues
news.para: A bench of Justices DY Chandrachud and MR Shah directed that the meeting be held on the weekend and formulations so prepared be placed before the court on the next date of hearing so that necessary orders could be passed.
